mrl-deskbook pack — content licence
====================================

This pack is derived from:
    Manufacturing Readiness Level (MRL) Deskbook
    Version 2022 (1 October 2022 update)
    Prepared by the Office of the Secretary of Defense Manufacturing Technology
    Program (OSD ManTech), in collaboration with the Joint Service/Industry
    MRL Working Group.

Source licence: Public Domain (US Government work); Distribution A — Approved for
public release; distribution unlimited.  (tier 1 — see ../../docs/SOURCE-VETTING.md)
No source-material download link is published (see ../../docs/LICENSING.md).

This source is a work of the United States Government, prepared by/for the Department
of Defense, and is therefore NOT subject to copyright protection in the United States
(17 U.S.C. 105). It is marked Distribution A (approved for public release; distribution
unlimited) and may be reproduced and distributed without further permission.

ADVISORY-STATUS NOTICE (reproduced from the source). The Deskbook's own front matter
states:

    "This document is not a DoD requirement and is offered as a best practice."

Accordingly, this pack is advisory, not a mandate. Nothing in it overrides DoD policy,
statute, the Federal Acquisition Regulation (FAR), or the Defense Federal Acquisition
Regulation Supplement (DFARS). The MRL criteria are descriptive (they state what
maturity looks like) and do not, by themselves, task any contractor to perform work.

SEPARATELY DISTRIBUTED ARTIFACTS. The authoritative MRL Criteria Matrix (Appendix A)
and the Microsoft Excel MRL Users Guide are maintained and distributed separately by
the MRL Working Group (historically via the DoD MRL website). This pack does NOT
reproduce their cell-by-cell criteria text; it carries the framework and how to use it.

Caveat: any DoD publication may incorporate third-party copyrighted images or material
whose separate reproduction could require permission from the copyright holder. This
pack reproduces no such third-party material — it contains only synthesized, transformed
reference notes — so the caveat does not apply to this pack's content.

Attribution to OSD ManTech and the Joint Service/Industry MRL Working Group is provided
as a courtesy (see the repository NOTICE), not a legal obligation. The Working Group
does not endorse this pack or its authors.

NOTE: This file governs the CONTENT of this pack. The repository tooling is licensed
separately under MIT (see ../../LICENSE).
